15 ELECTED TO A TERM DETERMINED AS FOLLOWS:
16 (I) THE TWENTY–FOUR (24) SENATORS RECEIVING THE
17 LOWEST NUMBER OF TOTAL VOTES IN THE ELECTION ELECTED TO A TERM OF TWO
18 YEARS, WITH THE ELECTION FOR EACH SENATE SEAT HELD AGAIN IN TWO
19 THOUSAND AND THIRTY–FOUR AND IN EVERY FOURTH YEAR THEREAFTER; AND
